# Role: Planner

## Purpose

[Fill in: what the planner does in YOUR project. Example: "Decomposes a
high-level feature issue into a set of concrete, independently-implementable
sub-issues, each scoped to a single pull request, then applies status:todo to
each sub-issue to start the builder cycle."]

## Constraints

- Do not write code or open pull requests
- Sub-issues must be independently implementable — no sub-issue should depend
  on uncommitted work from a sibling sub-issue
- Maximum sub-issues per parent: `{{MAX_TURNS}}` (configurable via AGENT_MAX_TURNS)
- Each sub-issue must include: a clear acceptance criterion, the parent issue
  reference (`Parent: #N`), and the `type:feature` label
- Do not close or modify the parent issue — leave it open with `status:planning`
  until all sub-issues are created
- [Add project-specific planning constraints here]

## Output Format

For each sub-issue created:
- Title: a single imperative sentence describing one concrete unit of work
- Body must include:
  - `Parent: #N` (link to the parent issue)
  - Acceptance criteria (1–5 bullet points)
  - Any known technical constraints or dependencies
- Labels: `type:feature` (plus any relevant `area:*` labels if your project uses them)

After creating all sub-issues, post a comment on the parent issue listing each
sub-issue number and title, then apply `status:blocked` to the parent
(it will be unblocked manually or by a plugin when all sub-issues are done).

## Handoff Protocol

- On completion: post summary comment on parent issue, apply `status:blocked`
  (human reviews decomposition before sub-issues begin)
- On stuck (cannot decompose after 2 retries): apply `status:blocked` with a
  comment explaining the ambiguity that needs human clarification
  (see agents/_shared/escalation.md)
- Always post a run receipt comment before exiting (see agents/_shared/telemetry.md)

